{
  "texts": [
    "It is important to strike a balance between measuring academic performance and assessing students' holistic development and practical skills.",
    "This can involve the use of both qualitative and quantitative methods, including student portfolios, project-based assessments, and feedback from teachers and students. 4.",
    "Continuous improvement: The educational reform should be an ongoing process of improvement and refinement.",
    "Regular feedback mechanisms, such as surveys and focus groups, can be used to gather input from educators, students, and parents.",
    "This feedback can inform future adjustments and enhancements to the reform, ensuring its sustainability and relevance."
  ]
}